9:T954,6) Put controls, procedures, and processes in place: The implementation must start as soon as processes are specified and procedures are created. Give a timeline and a description of the implementation strategy. Identify any updated staff expectations and communicate them. What adjustments will have an impact on daily life? What safeguards are now included in the procedures? How will the business make sure that the standard operating procedures are being followed and processes are being carried out as intended? Create a strategy for tracking implementation and evaluating the performance of established procedures. Records should be created and checked on occasion. 7) Implement training and awareness initiatives: Every employee needs to know about ISO 17025 certification, but they also need to know what is expected of them. A need for information exchange is unavoidable when change is imminent. Make sure to emphasize the adjustments that will be made to routine tasks. Committees or small groups might be used as awareness-raising programmes to help propagate future expectations. 8) Communicate with the accreditation organization: Get in touch with your accreditation body. Your laboratory can only get accredited through the assessment procedure with the help of an accreditation authority, which also supplies the necessary tools. Start communicating with one of the best ISO certification body in UAE, WIZMS. 9) Run the LMS: The core of all operations pertaining to everyday operations is the Laboratory Management System (LMS) as outlined by the quality objectives and procedures. Once the LMS is in place, you should continue to educate the personnel about the requirements and examine the relevant records to make sure the system is operating as intended. 10) Behavior internal reviews. ISO 17025 Internal audits should be used to assess the quality management system in relation to both the established SOPs and the requirements of the standard. The purpose of internal auditing procedures and the frequency at which it occurs should be known to the staff. 11) Management evaluation. WIZMS, ISO 17025 certification consultant in Dubai determines how frequently these reviews are conducted. Resources, risks and opportunities, nonconformance, and every facet of the management system's functionality should all be adequately covered in the management review's content.4:["$","p","5",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"$9"}]
